content.text: Phase 3 of the project involves intervention analysis for a few specific events. To make the most out of it, these events should have a few characteristics:
Large scale
Significant prior belief of impact
Well-defined start date
An easily defined KPI for measurement

We want to begin brainstorming events that match those characteristics as closely as possible. The better an event fits those criteria, the clearer the impact measurement will be. The overarching theme of these criteria is granularity  both in measurement and intervention.
There are two purposes of the pre-discovery:
Discuss the above criteria and answer any questions around them to determine appropriate levels of granularity.
Discuss business/use cases.
